# =============================================================================
# Kianax Environment Variables - Reference Guide
# =============================================================================
# This monorepo uses CO-LOCATED .env.local files. Each app manages its own
# environment variables. See the .env.example in each app directory:
#
#   apps/web/.env.example       - Next.js frontend
#   apps/workers/.env.example   - Temporal workers
#   apps/scripts/.env.example   - Test scripts and CLI tools
#   apps/server/.env.example    - Convex (uses dashboard, not files)
#
# =============================================================================
# QUICK REFERENCE
# =============================================================================

# --- Web App (apps/web/.env.local) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud
# TEMPORAL_ADDRESS=localhost:7233
# TEMPORAL_NAMESPACE=default
# SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...                    (optional - AI chat features)
# TEMPORAL_CLIENT_CERT=<base64>            (optional - Temporal Cloud)
# TEMPORAL_CLIENT_KEY=<base64>             (optional - Temporal Cloud)

# --- Workers (apps/workers/.env.local) ---
# CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud
# TEMPORAL_ADDRESS=localhost:7233
# TEMPORAL_NAMESPACE=default
# TASK_QUEUE=default                       (optional)
# TEMPORAL_CLIENT_CERT=<base64>            (optional - Temporal Cloud)
# TEMPORAL_CLIENT_KEY=<base64>             (optional - Temporal Cloud)

# --- Scripts (apps/scripts/.env.local) ---
# CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud
# TEMPORAL_ADDRESS=localhost:7233
# TEMPORAL_NAMESPACE=default

# --- Convex Server (set via dashboard or CLI, NOT .env files) ---
# npx convex env set SITE_URL http://localhost:3000
# npx convex env set CONVEX_SITE_URL https://your-deployment.convex.site
# npx convex env set GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID <your-google-client-id>
# npx convex env set GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET <your-google-client-secret>

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Start Convex development server:
#    cd apps/server && npx convex dev
#    (This will give you the CONVEX_URL / NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL)
#
# 2. Copy .env.example to .env.local in each app:
#    cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local
#    cp apps/workers/.env.example apps/workers/.env.local
#    cp apps/scripts/.env.example apps/scripts/.env.local
#
# 3. Set Convex env vars via CLI:
#    npx convex env set SITE_URL http://localhost:3000
#    npx convex env set CONVEX_SITE_URL <your-convex-site-url>
#    npx convex env set GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID <your-client-id>
#    npx convex env set GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET <your-client-secret>
#
# 4. Start development:
#    bun run dev:temporal   (Terminal 1 - Temporal server)
#    bun run dev:apps       (Terminal 2 - All apps)
